# Ruby Gem Conventions

## YARD docs on all public methods
```ruby
# ✅ GOOD
# @param name [String] the user's name
# @return [String] a greeting
def greet(name)
  "Hello, #{name}"
end

# ❌ BAD — no YARD doc on public method
def greet(name)
  "Hello, #{name}"
end
```

## Custom errors inherit from MyGem::Error
```ruby
# ✅ GOOD
module MyGem
  class NotFoundError < Error; end
end

# ❌ BAD — inheriting from StandardError directly
class NotFoundError < StandardError; end
```

## Configuration via MyGem.configuration
```ruby
# ✅ GOOD
MyGem.configure do |config|
  config.timeout = 30
end

# ❌ BAD — global variables or class variables for config
$my_gem_timeout = 30
```

## Test file mirrors lib file
lib/my_gem/foo.rb → spec/my_gem/foo_spec.rb (always, no exceptions)
